  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-8 clean envelope)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. The operating envelope is explicitly bounded (flow 1–7 L/min, rotational speed 2000–4500 RPM, hematocrit 35–45 %, inlet pressure 5–15 mmHg) and validation experiments densely cover this envelope. All 13 credibility factors are assessed with achieved levels meeting or exceeding required levels. Decision: Accepted.",
