  "hasSensitivityAnalysis": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/sensitivity/hemolysis-sa-001",
    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "Global sensitivity analysis — hemolysis power-law and turbulence model parameters",
    "description": "Sobol first-order and total-effect indices computed across six uncertain inputs: hemolysis power-law coefficient C (±15 %), exponents α and β (±10 % each), turbulence model constant Cμ (±8 %), inlet hematocrit (±5 %), and impeller tip clearance (±0.05 mm). The power-law coefficient C dominates hemolysis output variance (S_T = 0.61), followed by exponent α (S_T = 0.22); turbulence and geometric parameters contribute less than 5 % each, confirming that model-form uncertainty in the hemolysis constitutive law is the primary driver and justifying targeted experimental characterisation of that parameter."
  },
